  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">AWD response and prevention in East Harerghie zone in Oromia region, Fafan and Errer Zones of Somali Region and  South Gondar of Amhara Region</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is to respond to the ongoing epidemic of acute watery diarrhea (AWD) in Fafan and Errer Zones in Somali Region and the South Gonder Zone in Amhara Region and East Hararghe of Oromia region. The project will support households with hygiene and sanitation awareness as well as NFIs ( soaps, jeri-cans, water purifiers)  to prevent the spread of AWD. It will also support the local government and health institutions to cope with AWD by providing materials and support to strengthen CTCs the functioning of strengthening existing  CTCs and establishment of new ones if required. In the case of East Hararghe, water rehabilitation will be carried out in two woredas affected by water shortages and/or high cases of AWD.</narrative>
  </description>
